The paper discusses the number of citations in the Data Citation Index, which is a database of research data. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on data citation and indexing, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
